This paper deals with program verification and the use of equational systems, which suggests it could belong to the Logic (cs.LO) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper specifically mentions the combination of Boolean algebra and Kleene algebra, which are topics within Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the encoding of Hoare logic, which is a formal system for program verification, indicating that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
